dom-svgclippathelement-clippathunits.name: clipPathUnits
dom-svgclippathelement-clippathunits.summary: The read-only clipPathUnits property of the SVGClipPathElement interface reflects the clipPathUnits attribute of a <clipPath> element which defines the coordinate system to use for the content of the element.
dom-svgclippathelement-clippathunits.title: SVGClipPathElement: clipPathUnits property

dom-svgclippathelement-transform.name: transform
dom-svgclippathelement-transform.summary: The read-only transform property of the SVGClipPathElement interface reflects the transform attribute of a <clipPath> element, that is a list of transformations applied to the element.
dom-svgclippathelement-transform.title: SVGClipPathElement: transform property

InterfaceSVGClipPathElement.name: SVGClipPathElement
InterfaceSVGClipPathElement.summary: The SVGClipPathElement interface provides access to the properties of <clipPath> elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.
InterfaceSVGClipPathElement.title: SVGClipPathElement

dom-svgmaskelement-height.name: height
dom-svgmaskelement-height.summary: The read-only height property of the SVGMaskElement interface returns an SVGAnimatedLength object containing the value of the height attribute of the <marker>.
dom-svgmaskelement-height.title: SVGMaskElement: height property

dom-svgmaskelement-maskcontentunits.name: maskContentUnits
dom-svgmaskelement-maskcontentunits.summary: The read-only maskContentUnits property of the SVGMaskElement interface reflects the maskContentUnits attribute. It indicates which coordinate system to use for the contents of the <mask> element.
dom-svgmaskelement-maskcontentunits.title: SVGMaskElement: maskContentUnits property

dom-svgmaskelement-maskunits.name: maskUnits
dom-svgmaskelement-maskunits.summary: The read-only maskUnits property of the SVGMaskElement interface reflects the maskUnits attribute of a <mask> element which defines the coordinate system to use for the mask of the element.
dom-svgmaskelement-maskunits.title: SVGMaskElement: maskUnits property

dom-svgmaskelement-width.name: width
dom-svgmaskelement-width.summary: The read-only width property of the SVGMaskElement interface returns an SVGAnimatedLength object containing the value of the width attribute of the <marker>.
dom-svgmaskelement-width.title: SVGMaskElement: width property

dom-svgmaskelement-x.name: x
dom-svgmaskelement-x.summary: The read-only x property of the SVGMaskElement interface returns an SVGAnimatedLength object containing the value of the x attribute of the <mask>. It represents the x-axis coordinate of the top-left corner of the masking area.
dom-svgmaskelement-x.title: SVGMaskElement: x property

dom-svgmaskelement-y.name: y
dom-svgmaskelement-y.summary: The read-only y property of the SVGMaskElement interface returns an SVGAnimatedLength object containing the value of the y attribute of the <marker>. It represents the y-axis coordinate of the top-left corner of the masking area.
dom-svgmaskelement-y.title: SVGMaskElement: y property

InterfaceSVGMaskElement.name: SVGMaskElement
InterfaceSVGMaskElement.summary: The SVGMaskElement interface provides access to the properties of <mask> elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.
InterfaceSVGMaskElement.title: SVGMaskElement

the-clip-path.name: clip-path
the-clip-path.summary: The clip-path CSS property creates a clipping region that sets what part of an element should be shown. Parts that are inside the region are shown, while those outside are hidden.

ie.notes: Only supports clip paths defined by url().

the-clip-path.title: clip-path

the-clip-path.name: clip-path
the-clip-path.summary: The clip-path presentation attribute defines or associates a clipping path with the element it is related to.
the-clip-path.title: clip-path

the-mask-border-outset.name: mask-border-outset
the-mask-border-outset.summary: The mask-border-outset CSS property specifies the distance by which an element's mask border is set out from its border box.
the-mask-border-outset.title: mask-border-outset

the-mask-border-repeat.name: mask-border-repeat
the-mask-border-repeat.summary: The mask-border-repeat CSS property sets how the edge regions of a source image are adjusted to fit the dimensions of an element's mask border.
the-mask-border-repeat.title: mask-border-repeat

the-mask-border-slice.name: mask-border-slice
the-mask-border-slice.summary: The mask-border-slice CSS property divides the image set by mask-border-source into regions. These regions are used to form the components of an element's mask border.
the-mask-border-slice.title: mask-border-slice

the-mask-border-source.name: mask-border-source
the-mask-border-source.summary: The mask-border-source CSS property sets the source image used to create an element's mask border.
the-mask-border-source.title: mask-border-source

the-mask-border-width.name: mask-border-width
the-mask-border-width.summary: The mask-border-width CSS property sets the width of an element's mask border.
the-mask-border-width.title: mask-border-width

the-mask-border.name: mask-border
the-mask-border.summary: The mask-border CSS shorthand property lets you create a mask along the edge of an element's border.
the-mask-border.title: mask-border

the-mask-clip.name: mask-clip
the-mask-clip.summary: The mask-clip CSS property determines the area which is affected by a mask. The painted content of an element must be restricted to this area.
the-mask-clip.title: mask-clip

the-mask-composite.name: mask-composite
the-mask-composite.summary: The mask-composite CSS property represents a compositing operation used on the current mask layer with the mask layers below it.

chrome.notes: See also -webkit-mask-composite for a similar non-standard property that uses different keywords.

safari.notes: See also -webkit-mask-composite for a similar non-standard property that uses different keywords.

edge_blink.notes: See also -webkit-mask-composite for a similar non-standard property that uses different keywords.

the-mask-composite.title: mask-composite

the-mask-image.name: mask-image
the-mask-image.summary: The mask-image CSS property sets the image that is used as mask layer for an element. By default this means the alpha channel of the mask image will be multiplied with the alpha channel of the element. This can be controlled with the mask-mode property.

chrome.notes: From version 8, Chrome added support for gradient values. Initially, Chrome supported only -webkit- prefixed values for gradients (such as -webkit-linear-gradient()). Later, support for unprefixed values was added.

safari.notes: Initially, Safari supported only -webkit- prefixed values for gradients (such as -webkit-linear-gradient()). Later, support for unprefixed values was added.

webview_android.notes: Initially, Android supported only -webkit- prefixed values for gradients (such as -webkit-linear-gradient()). Later, support for unprefixed values was added.

edge_blink.notes: From version 8, Chrome added support for gradient values. Initially, Chrome supported only -webkit- prefixed values for gradients (such as -webkit-linear-gradient()). Later, support for unprefixed values was added.

the-mask-image.title: mask-image

the-mask-mode.name: mask-mode
the-mask-mode.summary: The mask-mode CSS property sets whether the mask reference defined by mask-image is treated as a luminance or alpha mask.
the-mask-mode.title: mask-mode

the-mask-origin.name: mask-origin
the-mask-origin.summary: The mask-origin CSS property sets the origin of a mask.
the-mask-origin.title: mask-origin

the-mask-position.name: mask-position
the-mask-position.summary: The mask-position CSS property sets the initial position, relative to the mask position layer set by mask-origin, for each defined mask image.
the-mask-position.title: mask-position

the-mask-repeat.name: mask-repeat
the-mask-repeat.summary: The mask-repeat CSS property sets how mask images are repeated. A mask image can be repeated along the horizontal axis, the vertical axis, both axes, or not repeated at all.
the-mask-repeat.title: mask-repeat

the-mask-size.name: mask-size
the-mask-size.summary: The mask-size CSS property specifies the sizes of the mask images. The size of the image can be fully or partially constrained in order to preserve its intrinsic ratio.
the-mask-size.title: mask-size

the-mask-type.name: mask-type
the-mask-type.summary: The mask-type CSS property sets whether an SVG <mask> element is used as a luminance or an alpha mask. It applies to the <mask> element itself.
the-mask-type.title: mask-type

the-mask.name: mask
the-mask.summary: The mask CSS shorthand property hides an element (partially or fully) by masking or clipping the image at specific points.

chrome.notes: While the property is recognized, values applied to it don't have any effect.
The prefixed property can be used with SVG and HTML with a slightly different syntax, which allows setting the non-standard -webkit-mask-attachment property.

firefox.notes: From Firefox 10, the default color space when handling masks is sRGB. Previously, the default and only supported color space was linear RGB. This changes the appearance of mask effects, but brings Firefox into compliance with the second edition of the SVG 1.1 specification.

safari.notes: While the property is recognized, values applied to it don't have any effect.
The prefixed property can be used with SVG and HTML with a slightly different syntax, which allows setting the non-standard -webkit-mask-attachment property.

webview_android.notes: While the property is recognized, values applied to it don't have any effect.
The prefixed property can be used with SVG and HTML with a slightly different syntax, which allows setting the non-standard -webkit-mask-attachment property.

edge_blink.notes: While the property is recognized, values applied to it don't have any effect.
The prefixed property can be used with SVG and HTML with a slightly different syntax, which allows setting the non-standard -webkit-mask-attachment property.

the-mask.title: mask

the-mask.name: mask
the-mask.summary: The mask attribute is a presentation attribute mainly used to bind a given <mask> element with the element the attribute belongs to.
the-mask.title: mask

ClipPathElement.name: clipPath
ClipPathElement.summary: The <clipPath> SVG element defines a clipping path, to be used by the clip-path property.
ClipPathElement.title: <clipPath>

element-attrdef-mask-maskcontentunits.name: maskContentUnits
element-attrdef-mask-maskcontentunits.summary: The maskContentUnits attribute indicates which coordinate system to use for the contents of the <mask> element.
element-attrdef-mask-maskcontentunits.title: maskContentUnits

element-attrdef-mask-maskunits.name: maskUnits
element-attrdef-mask-maskunits.summary: The maskUnits attribute indicates which coordinate system to use for the geometry properties of the <mask> element.
element-attrdef-mask-maskunits.title: maskUnits

MaskElement.name: mask
MaskElement.summary: The <mask> element defines an alpha mask for compositing the current object into the background. A mask is used/referenced using the mask property.
MaskElement.title: <mask>
